race.comment: RHYTHMIC ENERGY (2) boasts a strong record this course with three wins and two minors from nine tries. Placed last time (29.89) at this track in a Grade 4/5, finishing third and beaten 5.5 lengths. Looks a key chance on best form. ASTON GOZO (3) goes very well this course and distance starting 10 times for four wins and four minors. Missed the frame latest (31.15) when sixth over 531m at Gawler in a OPEN. Suited here and expected to run well. TALCOTT BALE (4) had the drop on the lead before drawing clear to score (29.66) at this track in a Grade 4/5 over 515m. Has a strong record out of this box with seven wins and five minor placings from 16 starts. One of the prime contenders. SIT AND STEER (1) was in the money last start from this box - poses a threat again.
